The paper deals with the formalization of parametric polymorphism for System F, which is a topic in the intersection of logic (LO) and programming languages (PL). The use of cubical categories is a relatively new development in category theory (CT) that has been applied to programming language theory. The paper also deals with technical issues in the bifibrational treatment of relational parametricity, which is a topic in semantics (SE) and type theory (IT).
